<div class="comment">
 <h3 class="title"><a href="node/646#comment-5565" class="active">Models-of-computation-centrism versus language-centrism</a></h3>
 <div class="content"><p >I'd say that the formulae-as-types correspondence is important to the language-centric view of computation, but not so important to the models-of-computation-centric view of theoretical computer science which has the upper hand in theory and is favoured on the Vardi view.  The latter view has the more compelling story to say about <i >why</i> the science of computation needs powerful abstractions to yield its secrets, IMO.</p></div>
